obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (21240)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 38
  title `Special provisions for registration of certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21240&sectionno=32A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[32A. Special provisions for registration of certain persons.--(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 32, a State Council may also permit to be entered on the register--`
  line
  line `(a) the names of displaced persons who have been carrying on the business or profession of`
  line `pharmacy as their principal means of livelihood from a date prior to the 4th day of March, 1948, and`
  line `who satisfy the conditions for registration as set out in section 31;`
  line
  line `(b) the names of citizens of India who have been carrying on the business or profession of`
  line `pharmacy in any country outside India and who satisfy the conditions for registration as set out in`
  line `section 31;`
  line
  line `(c) the names of persons who resided in an area which has subsequently become a territory of`
  line `India and who satisfy the conditions for registration as set out in section 31;`
  line
  line `(d) the names of persons who carry on the business or profession of pharmacy in the State, and`
  line
  line `(i) would have satisfied the conditions for registration as set out in section 31, on the date`
  line `appointed under sub-section (2) of section 30, had they applied for registration on or before that`
  line `date; or`
  line
  line `(ii) have been engaged in the compounding of drugs in a hospital or dispensary or other place`
  line `in which drugs are regularly dispensed on prescriptions of medical practitioners as defined in`
  line `sub-clause (iii) of clause (f) of section 2 for a total period of not less than five years prior to the`
  line `date appointed under sub-section (2) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(e) the names of persons who were qualified to be entered in the register for a State as it existed`
  line `immediately before the 1st day of November, 1956, but who, by reason of the area in which they`
  line `resided or carried on their business or profession of pharmacy having become part of a State as`
  line `formed on that date, are not qualified to be entered in the register for the latter State only by reason of`
  line `their not having passed either a matriculation examination or an examination prescribed as being`
  line `equivalent to a matriculation examination of an approved examination or of their not possessing a`
  line `qualification approved under section 14;`
  line
  line `(f) the names of persons--`
  line
  line `(i) who were included in the register for a State as it existed immediately before the 1st day of`
  line `November, 1956; and`
  line
  line `(ii) who, by reason of the area in which they resided or carried on their business or profession`
  line `of pharmacy having become part of a State as formed on that date, reside or carry on such`
  line `business or profession in the latter State;`
  line
  line `(g) the names of persons who reside or carry on their business or profession of pharmacy in an`
  line `area in which this Chapter takes effect after the commencement of the Pharmacy (Amendment) Act,`
  line `1959 (24 of 1959), and who satisfy the conditions for registration as set out in section 31.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who desires his name to be entered in the register in pursuance of sub-section (1) shall`
  line `make an application in that behalf to the State Council, and such application shall be accompanied by the`
  line `prescribed fee.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall remain in operation for a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of the Pharmacy (Amendment) Act, 1959 (24 of 1959):`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, extend the period of`
  line `operation of clause (a), clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) by such further period or periods, not`
  line `exceeding two years in the aggregate, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of clause (a) of sub-section (1), "displaced person" means any`
  line `person who on account of the setting up of the Dominions of India and Pakistan or on account of civil`
  line `disturbances or the fear of such disturbances in any area now forming part of Pakistan, has, on or after the`
  line `1st day of March, 1947, left or been displaced from his place of residence in such area and who has since`
  line `then been residing in India.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of clauses (b), (c) and (g) of sub-section (1), the period referred to`
  line `in clause (d) of section 31 shall be computed with reference to the date of application.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b:
  sectionId (21241)
  sectionNo 32B
  orderNo 39
  title `Special provisions for registration of displaced persons, repatriates and other persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 70 of 1976, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-9-1976)./`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21241&sectionno=32B&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[32B. Special provisions for registration of displaced persons, repatriates and other persons.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 32 or section 32A, a State Council may permit to be`
  line `entered on the register--`
  line
  line `(a) the names of persons who possess the qualification specified in clause (a) or clause (c) of`
  line `section 31 and who were eligible for registration between the closing of the First Register and the date`
  line `when the Education Regulations came into effect.`
  line
  line `(b) the names of persons approved as qualified persons before the 31st December, 1969 for`
  line `compounding or dispensing of medicines under the Drugs and Cosmetics Act, 1940 (23 of 1940), and`
  line `the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(c) the names of displaced persons or repatriates who were carrying on business or profession of`
  line `pharmacy as their principal means of livelihood in any country outside India for a total period of not`
  line `less than five years from a date prior to the date of application for registration.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "displaced person" means any person who, on account of civil disturbances or the fear of such`
  line `disturbances in any area now forming part of Bangla Desh, has, after the 14th day of April, 1957 but`
  line `before the 25th day of March, 1971, left, or has been displaced from, his place of residence in such`
  line `area and who has since then been residing in India;`
  line
  line `(ii) "repatriate" means any person of Indian origin who, on account of civil disturbances or the`
  line `fear of such disturbances in any area now forming part of Burma, Sri Lanka or Uganda, or any other`
  line `country has, after the 14th day of April, 1957, left or has been displaced from, his place of residence`
  line `in such area and who has since then been residing in India.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1) shall remain in operation for a period of`
  line `two years from the commencement of the Pharmacy (Amendment) Act, 1976 (70 of 1976).]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir (UT).--`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section--After section 32B, insert--`
  line
  line `"32C. Special provisions regarding persons registered under Jammu and Kashmir Pharmacy`
  line `Act, Samvat, 2011 (1955 A.D.).--Notwithstanding anything contained in section 32, any person whose`
  line `name has been entered in the register of pharmacists maintained under the Jammu and Kashmir Pharmacy`
  line `Act, 2011 (1955 A.D.) and possesses qualification prescribed under the said Act shall be deemed to have`
  line `been entered in the register of pharmacists prepared and maintained under Chapter IV of this Act, subject to an application to be made in this behalf within a period of one year commencing from 31st October,`
  line `2020 and payment of such fee as may be prescribed by the Government of Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir."`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order,`
  line `2020, notification No. S.O. 3465(E), dated (5-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Ladakh (UT).--`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section--After section 32B, insert--`
  line
  line `"32C. Special provisions regarding persons registered under Jammu and Kashmir Pharmacy Act,`
  line `Samvat, 2011 (1955 A.D.).--Notwithstanding anything contained in section 32, any person whose name has`
  line `been entered in the register of pharmacists maintained under the Jammu and Kashmir Pharmacy Act, 2011`
  line `(1955 A.D.) and possesses qualification prescribed under the said Act shall be deemed to have been entered in`
  line `the register of pharmacists prepared and maintained under Chapter IV of this Act, subject to an application to`
  line `be made in this behalf within a period of one year commencing from 1st day of the January, 2020 and payment`
  line `of such fee as may be prescribed by the Administration of the Union territory of Ladakh."`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_c:
  sectionId (76554)
  sectionNo 32C
  orderNo 40
  title `Special provision relating to persons registered or qualified under Jammu and Kashmir Pharmacy Act, 2011.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=76554&sectionno=32C&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_32_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[32C. Special provision relating to persons registered or qualified under Jammu and Kashmir Pharmacy`
  line `Act, 2011.Notwithstanding anything contained in section 32, any person whose name has been entered in the`
  line `register of pharmacists maintained under the Jammu and Kashmir Pharmacy Act, 2011 (Jammu and Kashmir Act`
  line `no. LIII of 2011 (1955 A.D.). or possesses qualification (medical assistant/pharmacists) prescribed under the said`
  line `Act shall be deemed to have been entered in the register of pharmacists prepared and maintained under Chapter IV`
  line `of this Act, subject to condition that an application to be made in this behalf within a period of one year from the`
  line `commencement of the Pharmacy (Amendment) Act, 2023 and on payment of such fee, and in such manner, as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Administration of Union territory of`
  line Ladakh.]
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (21242)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 41
  title `Scrutiny of applications for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21242&sectionno=33&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the date appointed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 30, applications for registration shall be addressed to the Registrar of the State Council and shall`
  line `be accompanied by the prescribed fee.`
  line
  line `(2) If upon such application the Registrar is of opinion that the applicant is entitled to have his name`
  line `entered in the register under the provisions of this Act for the time being applicable, he shall enter the`
  line `name of the applicant in the register:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person whose name has under the provisions of this Act been removed from the`
  line `register of any State shall be entitled to have his name entered in the register except with the approval of`
  line `the State Council recorded at a meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person whose application for registration is rejected by the Registrar, may within three`
  line `months from the date of such rejection appeal to the State Council, and the decision of the State Council`
  line `thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon entry in the register of a name under this section, the Registrar shall issue a certificate of`
  line `registration in the prescribed form.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (21243)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 42
  title `Renewal fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21243&sectionno=34&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that`
  line `for the retention of a name on the register after the 31st day of December of the year following the year in`
  line `which the name is first entered on the register, there shall be paid annually to the State Council such`
  line `renewal fee as may be prescribed, and where such direction has been made, such renewal fee shall be due`
  line `to be paid before the first day of April of the year to which it relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a renewal fee is not paid by the due date, the Registrar shall remove the name of the`
  line `defaulter from the register:`
  line
  line `Provided that a name so removed may be restored to the register on such conditions as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) On payment of the renewal fee, the Registrar shall ^1[issue a receipt therefore and such receipt shall`
  line `be proof of renewal of registration].`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1959, s. 12, for "in the prescribed manner endorse the certificate of registration accordingly"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (21244)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 43
  title `Entry of additional qualifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21244&sectionno=35&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `A registered pharmacist shall on payment of the prescribed`
  line `fee be entitled to have entered in the register any further degrees or diplomas in pharmacy or`
  line `pharmaceutical chemistry which he may obtain.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (21245)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 44
  title `Removal from register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21245&sectionno=36&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, the Executive Committee`
  line `may order that the name of a registered pharmacist shall be removed from the register, where it is`
  line `satisfied, after giving him a reasonable opportunity of being heard and after such further inquiry, if any, as`
  line `it may think fit to make,--`
  line
  line `(i) that his name has been entered in the register by error or on account of misrepresentation or`
  line `suppression of a material fact, or`
  line
  line `(ii) that he has been convicted of any offence or has been guilty of any infamous conduct in any`
  line `professional respect which in the opinion of the Executive Committee, renders him unfit to be kept in`
  line `the register, or`
  line
  line `(iii) that a person employed by him for the purposes of his business of pharmacy ^1[or employed to`
  line `work under him in connection with any business of pharmacy] has been convicted of any such`
  line `offence or has been guilty of any such infamous conduct as would, if such person were a registered`
  line `pharmacist, render him liable to have his name removed from the register under clause (ii):`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under clause (iii) unless the Executive Committee is`
  line satisfied--
  line
  line `(a) that the offence or infamous conduct was instigated or connived at by the registered`
  line `pharmacist, or`
  line
  line `(b) that the registered pharmacist has at any time during the period of twelve months immediately`
  line `preceding the date on which the offence or infamous conduct took place committed a similar offence`
  line `or been guilty of similar infamous conduct, or`
  line
  line `(c) that any person employed by the registered pharmacist for the purposes of his business of`
  line `pharmacy ^2[or employed to work under him in connection with any business of pharmacy] has at any`
  line `time during the period of twelve months immediately preceding the date on which the offence or`
  line `infamous conduct took place, committed a similar offence or been guilty of similar infamous conduct,`
  line `and that the registered pharmacist had, or reasonably ought to have had, knowledge of such previous`
  line `offence or infamous conduct, or`
  line
  line `(d) that where the offence or infamous conduct continued over a period, the registered pharmacist`
  line `had, or reasonably ought to have had, knowledge of the continuing offence or infamous conduct, or`
  line
  line `(e) that where the offence is an offence under the ^3[Drugs and Cosmetics Act, 1940`
  line `(23 of 1940)], the registered pharmacist has not used due diligence in enforcing compliance with the`
  line `provisions of that Act in his place of business and by persons employed by him 1^2[or by persons under`
  line `his control].`
  line
  line `(2) An order under sub-section (1) may direct that the person whose name is ordered to be removed`
  line `from the register shall be ineligible for registration in the State under this Act either permanently or for`
  line `such period as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) An order under sub-section (1) shall be subject to confirmation by the State Council and shall not`
  line `take effect until the expiry of three months from the date of such confirmation.`
  line
  line `(4) A person aggrieved by an order under sub-section (1) which has been confirmed by the State`
  line `Council may, within thirty days from the communication to him of such confirmation, appeal to the State`
  line `Government, and the order of the State Government upon such appeal shall be final.`
  line
  line `(5) A person whose name has been removed from the register under this section or under sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 34 shall forthwith surrender his certificate of registration to the Registrar, and the name so`
  line `removed shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 24 of 1959, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 70 of 1976, s. 18, for "Drugs Act, 1940 (23 of 1940)" (w.e.f. 1-9-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (21246)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 45
  title `Restoration to register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21246&sectionno=37&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The State Council may at any time for reasons appearing to it`
  line `sufficient order that upon payment of the prescribed fee the name of a person removed from the register`
  line `shall be restored thereto:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an appeal against such removal has been rejected by the State Government, an`
  line `order under this section shall not take effect until it has been confirmed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (21247)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 46
  title `Bar of other jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21247&sectionno=38&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No order refusing to enter a name on the register or removing a name`
  line `from the register shall be called in question in any Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (21248)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 47
  title `Issue of duplicate certificates of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21248&sectionno=39&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Where it is shown to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Registrar that a certificate of registration has been lost or destroyed, the Registrar may, on payment of the`
  line `prescribed fee, issue a duplicate certificate in the prescribed form.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (21249)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 48
  title `Printing of register and evidentiary value of entries therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1959, s. 14, for section 40 (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21249&sectionno=40&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `^1[40. Printing of register and evidentiary value of entries therein.--(1) As soon as may be after`
  line `the 1st day of April subsequent to the commencement of the Pharmacy (Amendment) Act, 1959`
  line `(24 of 1959), the Registrar shall cause to be printed copies of the register as it stood on the said date.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall thereafter cause to the printed as soon as may be after the 1st day of April in`
  line `each year copies of the annual supplement to the register referred to in sub-section (1), showing all`
  line `additions to, and other amendments in, the said register.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) The register shall be brought up-to-date three months before ordinary elections to the State`
  line `Council are held and copies of this register shall be printed.`
  line
  line `(b) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall apply to the register as so printed as they apply to the`
  line `register referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The copies referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) shall be made`
  line `available to persons applying therefor on payment of the prescribed charge and shall be evidence that on`
  line `the date referred to in the register or annual supplement, as the case may be, the persons whose names are`
  line `entered therein were registered pharmacist.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (21250)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 49
  title `Penalty for falsely claiming to be registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21250&sectionno=41&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) IIf any person whose name is not for the`
  line `time being entered in the register of the State falsely pretends that it is so entered or uses in connection with his name or title any words or letters reasonably calculated to suggest that his name is so entered, he`
  line `shall be punishable on first conviction with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and on subsequent`
  line `conviction with imprisonment which may extend to three months or with fine not exceeding two lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be a defence if the name of the person is entered in the register of another State`
  line `and that at the time of claim, an application for registration in the State had been made.]`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) it shall be immaterial whether or not any person is deceived by such pretence or use as`
  line aforesaid;
  line
  line `(b) the use of the description "pharmacist", "chemist", "druggist", "pharmaceutist", "dispenser",`
  line `"dispensing chemist", or any combination of such words ^2[or of any such word with any other word]`
  line `shall be deemed to be reasonably calculated to suggest that the person using such description is a`
  line `person whose name is for the time being entered in the register of the State.`
  line
  line `(c) the onus of proving that the name of a person is for the time being entered in the register of a`
  line `State shall be on him who asserts it.`
  line
  line `(3) Cognizance of an offence punishable under this section shall not be taken except upon complaint`
  line `made by order of the State Government or ^2[any officer authorized in this behalf by the State Government`
  line `or by order of] the Executive Committee of the State Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 31-12-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 24 of 1959, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (21251)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 50
  title `Dispensing by unregistered persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21251&sectionno=42&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) On or after such date as the State Government may`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette appoint in this behalf, no person other than a registered pharmacist`
  line `shall compound, prepare, mix, or dispense any medicine on the prescription of a medical practitioner ^1***;`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply to the dispensing by a medical practitioner of medicine`
  line `for his own patients, or with the general or special sanction of the State Government, for the patients of`
  line `another medical practitioner:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that where no such date is appointed by the Government of a State, this sub-section`
  line `shall take effect in that State on the expiry of a period of ^3[eight years] from the commencement of the`
  line `Pharmacy (Amendment) Act, 1976 (70 of 1976).]`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with ^4[imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to two lakh rupees, or with`
  line both].
  line
  line `(3) Cognizance of an offence punishable under this section shall not be taken except upon complaint`
  line `made by ^5[order of the State Government or any officer authorised in this behalf by the State Government,`
  line `or by order of the Executive Committee of the State Council.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except under the direct and personal supervision of a registered pharmacist" omitted by s. 16, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 70 of 1976, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-9-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 1982, s. 2, for "five years" (w.e.f. 1-9-1981).`
  line
  line `4.Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 31-12-2024).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 24 of 1959, s. 16, for "an order of the State Government" (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (21252)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 51
  title `Failure to surrender certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21252&sectionno=43&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person whose name has been`
  line `removed from the register fails without sufficient cause forthwith to surrender his certificate of`
  line `registration, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Cognizance of an offence punishable under this section shall not be taken except upon complaint`
  line `made by an order of the Executive Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43_a:
  sectionId (92541)
  sectionNo 43A
  orderNo 52
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=92541&sectionno=43A&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[43A. Adjudication of penalties.—(1) For the purposes of adjudging the penalties under section`
  line `26A, the Central Government shall authorise the President of the State council, Where the alleged`
  line `violation is committed, to be the adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry and impose penalty in the`
  line `manner as may be prescribed under section 18, after giving any person concerned a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever is aggrieved by any order of the adjudicating officer may prefer an appeal to the`
  line `President, Central Council, within a period of forty-five days from the date of receipt of such order in`
  line `such form and manner as may be prescribed under section 18.`
  line
  line `(3) The President, Central council may entertain an appeal after the expiry of forty-five days, if it is`
  line `satisfied that the appellant was prevented from sufficient cause for filling the appeal within the said`
  line period.
  line
  line `(4) No appeal shall be disposed of unless the appellant has been given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) An appeal under sub-section (2) shall be disposed of within ninety days from the date of filing.`
  line
  line `(6) The amount of penalty imposed under sub-section (1), if not paid, may be recovered as an arrear`
  line `of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (21253)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 53
  title `Payment of part of fees to Central Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21253&sectionno=44&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The State Council shall before the end of June in`
  line `each year pay to the Central Council a sum equivalent to one-fourth of the total fees realised by the State`
  line `Council under this Act during the period of twelve months ending on the 31st day of March of that year.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (21254)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 54
  title `Appointment of Commission of Enquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21254&sectionno=45&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it appears to the Central Government`
  line `that the Central Council is not complying with any of the provisions of this Act, the Central Government`
  line `may appoint a Commission of Enquiry consisting of three persons, two of whom shall be appointed by`
  line `the Central Government, one being the Judge of a High Court, and one by the Council; and refer to it the`
  line `matters on which the enquiry is to be made.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall proceed to enquire in such manner as it may deem fit and report to the`
  line `Central Government on the matters referred to it together with such remedies, if any, as the Commission`
  line `may like to recommend.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may accept the report or remit the same to the Commission for`
  line `modification or reconsideration.`
  line
  line `(4) After the report is finally accepted, the Central Government may order the Central Council to`
  line `adopt the remedies so recommended within such time as may be specified in the order and if the Council`
  line `fails to comply within the time so specified, the Central Government may pass such order or take such`
  line `action as may be necessary to give effect to the recommendations of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(5) Whenever it appears to the State Government that the State Council is not complying with any of`
  line `the provisions of this Act, the State Government may likewise appoint a similar Commission of Enquiry`
  line `and pass such order or take such action as specified in sub-sections (3) and (4).`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (21255)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458&sectionId=21255&sectionno=46&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00008_194808_1517807321458
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of Chapters III, IV and V.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the management of the property of the State Council, and the maintenance and audit of its`
  line accounts;
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which elections under Chapter III shall be conducted;`
  line
  line `(c) the summoning and holding of meetings of the State Council, the times and places at which`
  line `such meetings shall be held, the conduct of business thereat and the number of members necessary to`
  line `form a quorum;`
  line
  line `(d) the powers and duties of the President and Vice-President of the State Council;`
  line
  line `(e) the constitution and functions of the Executive Committee, the summoning and holding of`
  line `meetings thereof, the times and places at which such meetings shall be held, and the number of`
  line `members necessary to constitute a quorum;`
  line
  line `(f) the qualifications, the term of office and the powers and duties of the Registrar and other`
  line `officers and servants of the State Council, including the amount and nature of the security to be given`
  line `by the Treasurer;`
  line
  line `^1[(ff) the qualifications, powers and duties of an Inspector;]`
  line
  line `(g) the particulars to be stated, and the proof of qualifications to be given, in applications for`
  line `registration under Chapter IV;`
  line
  line `(h) the conditions for registration under sub-section (1) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(i) fees payable under Chapter IV and the charge for supplying copies of the register;`
  line
  line `(j) the form of certificates of registration ^2***;`
  line
  line `(k) the maintenance of a register;`
  line
  line `^3[(kk) the conduct of pharmacists and their duties in relation to medical practitioners, the public`
  line `and the profession of pharmacy;]`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed under Chapters III, IV and V except`
  line `sub-sections (1), (2), (3) and (4) of section 45.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 70 of 1976, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-9-1976).`
  line
  line `2. The words "and the manner of endorsement of renewals thereof" omitted by Act 24 of 1959, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
